JURA MOUNTAINS (France)

The Jura Mountains lie midway between Burgundy and Switzerland. The town of Arbois is the birthplace of Louis Pasteur, where he conducted his famous experi- ments and where some of the wines listed below are grown. The most intriguing certainly is the Chateau Chalon.
